properties.headline: Lakeshore Flood Advisory issued January 8 at 3:18PM CST until January 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Green Bay has issued a Lakeshore
Flood Advisory, which is in effect from midnight tonight to 9 PM
CST Thursday.

* LOCATIONS...Shorelines of Door, Kewaunee and Manitowoc
counties.

* LAKESHORE FLOODING...The combination of strong southeast to
south winds, waves building to 9 to 13 feet, and high lake
levels will result in localized flooding and erosion along the
Lake Michigan shoreline.

* TIMING...Midnight tonight through 9 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding on roads, parking lots and mouths of
rivers will be possible. Some beach erosion is also expected.
properties.instruction:
A Lakeshore Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds will
generate flooding of low areas along the lakeshore.

NWSheadline: LAKESHORE FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 9 PM CST THURSDAY
